ive it back!”, Mugman yelled. “How’re you able to move?”, it asked. “Uh…it IS my body, right??”, Mugman said. “I’m kinda like two-face.”, Mugman commented. “But…but I-“l the curse said, but Mugman cut him off. “Man, this guy inside me is annoying, but he’s also kinda weak.”, Mugman replied. “WEAK?! I’LL SHOW YOU WEAK!!”, it roared, but Mugman said, “SIR! I AM TRYING TO TALK TO MYSELF! SHUT UP!” “When I’m out of this body, you’ll be the first one I kill, you brat.”, it muttered. “Yeah, keep telling yourself that.”, Mugman said. “Mugman, don’t move. You’re no longer human. Under jujutsu regulations….i will exorcise the curse known as Mugman grace.”, Cuphead said. “Woah, Cuphead! Slow down! It’s not a problem. Furthermore, we’re both pretty messed up. We need a hospital or something.”, Mugman said with his hands up. “I can’t tell if that’s the curse or Mugman talking…damn, what should I do?!”, Cuphead thought. “What’s the situation?”, Lion asked. Cuphead then quickly turned around to see Lion, his teacher. “LION?! WHATRE YOU DOING HERE?!”, he yelled confused. “Well, I originally wasn’t gonna come, but after I heard about the cursed object, I came immediately. So, where is it?”, Lion stated, looking around casually. “Sorry…I ate it…”, Mugman said, walking over to Lion. “You’re not kidding. You have a curse inside you. Hmm…tell you what. Give up control to that curse inside you for…ten seconds. Then take control back. Got it?”, Lion asked. “Uh, okay…”, Mugman said. “But I’m not responsible for whatever this guy does in my body.”, Mugman added. “Hold this for me, Cuphead.”, Lion said, tossing Cuphead a bag. Cuphead caught it and looked inside. “Cookies? You were buying cookies while people were in danger??”, Cuphead asked annoyed. “Those are for the train ride home.”, Lion said. Then, the curse inside Mugman took control, and leaped up, preparing to attack Lion. Lion dodged, and the curse fell. “Since one of my students are watching, I’m gonna show off a bit. You don’t mind, right?”, Lion said, looking at the curse using Mugman. The curse frowned, before dashing away, and jumping back up into the air, swiping a claw at Lion. Lion dodged, and kicked the curse in the gut, before sending him flying into a wall. “8…9…10.”, Lion said aloud. Then, suddenly, The curses markings disappeared, and Mugman was back in control. “No way, you actually can control it!”, Lion said. “Yeah, but it’s kinda annoying. I can still hear his voice in my head.”, Mugman muttered. “That’s good. You can be a vessel.”, Lion said. Then, he swiftly knocked out Mugman. Mugman wakes up the next day, tied to a chair, with a bunch of papers with weird markings on the rope he’s tied with. “Wakes wakes, fingers and bakey.”, Lion said. “So, which one are you now?”, Lion asked. “Uh…it’s…me…Mugman.”, Mugman muttered. “Good. Time to break the news. And your decisions. Mugman…you’ve been set up for a secret execution.”, Lion said. “Huh?”, Mugman said. “Lemme explain. You see, Mugman, the cursed object that you had swallowed wasn’t a pickle. It was only one part of the king of curses; Jules. He was the strongest jujutsu sorcerer, and before he died, he had turned himself into twenty cursed objects. We have three, or four, counting the one side you. Here is one of the parts,” Lion said, pulling out a finger. Lion then threw it up into the air, and shot it with some cursed energy. “As you can see, it’s pretty tough, and also rare to find. And, with you swallowing one of those fingers, and not dying, you’ve become a vessel, with two options. One: we kill Jules inside you, and keep searching for the other fingers. Or…”, Lion said. “…or what?”, Mugman asked. “This is what I suggest. We find the rest of Jules-which is like…17 or 18 fingers-let him fully manifest inside you, and then execute you.” Lion proposed. “Either die right now, or die later, is basically what I’m asking.”, Lion said. “I…uh…”, Mugman stuttered. “…fine. I’ll eat the rest of Jules and then I’ll be executed.”, Mugman said. “Cool. Just know that in order to do this, you’ll have to enroll into Jujutsu High. And, acquire some cursed energy, and technique, and Domain Expansion, and cursed tool, and-“, Lion said, rambling on and on, before he saw Mugman just staring at him in confusion. “Let’s start with the school, first.”, Lion said, recognizing Mugmans confusion. We then cut to Lion and Mugman walking into the school. “Wow, this place looks very old. I can’t wait to make it look even uglier.”, Jules said, who had recently learned how to speak throw making little mouths on Mugman. “Sorry, Lion. He does that sometimes.”, Mugman said, covering the tiny mouth that Jules made. “It’s fine.”, Lion said. “Hey, Lion? I have a question.”, Mugman said, as they were walking towards the doors. “Between you and Jules…who would win?”, Mugman asked. Lion thought for a moment, before answering. “Well, if he were to get his full power back, he might cause me a little trouble.”, Lion said. Mugman asked, “but would you lose?” “Nah, I’d win.”, Lion said. “Tough talk coming from a brat.”, Jules said through one of the little mouths he had made on Mugman. Lion stopped walking, and asked, “what’s that supposed to mean?” “It’s just that you’re wrong. When I reach my peak status, not only will you not be able to handle me, but after I kill you, I’ll go after every single jujutsu sorcerer. Including this…brat I’m stuck inside currently.”, Jules said. “Wow, to be killed by the greatest curse in history. I’m touched.”, Lion said, sarcastically. After they talked with the principal, Mugman was enrolled. “Wait, so, how many sorcerers are at this school?”, Mugman said as Lion walked him to his room. “Like…eight students…”, Lion said nervously and awkwardly. “Oh.”, Mugman said. “But, some of your friends are here. Like, Alice, Bendy and Cuphead.”, Lion said. “Wait, what?! And they didn’t tell me?!”, Mugman said, angry. “Surprise.”, Lion said, before he opened Mugman room. “So, question for you, Mugman. Will 