ursed energy, along with knowledge of cursed….anything that can help you in battle. This includes domain expansion, cursed techniques, cursed tools, binding vows, and heavenly restrictions. In return…whenever I say the word, ‘Enchant’, I can take control of your body for up to five minutes tops. That’s all I ask.”, Jules said. “Hell no! How do I know that-“, Mugman yelled, before Jules cut him off by saying, “within that time frame, I’m not allowed to harm or injure anybody. Does that seal the deal?” Mugman thought for a moment, before asking, “anything else I should be aware about?” “You will forget that you made this deal with me.”, Jules added. “So, our deal goes as follows: I get knowledge about domain expansion, cursed techniques, cursed tools, binding vows, and heavenly restrictions. and you get to take control of my body for five minutes whenever you say the word ‘Enchant’. I forget that we made this deal, and you can’t harm or injure anybody while you possess me. Am I right?”, Mugman recounted. “Yup.”, Jules said casually. “Do we have a deal?”, Jules asked. Mugman thought about this. Mugman thought really hard. “Why do you want to take control of my body if you can’t hurt anyone?”, Mugman asked. Jules slightly panicked, before answering Mugman, saying, “Fine. I agree.” Jules grins, his teeth showing. “Excellent. See you soon, Mugman. Literally.”, Jules said, shaking Mugman hand, before the dream ends. Mugman then wakes up in the infirmary. “Hey, Mugman. You alright?”, Bendy says, standing on a wall. “Sorry that I attacked you yesterday. Lion wanted me to test you. See how good you were. I didn’t expect you to have cursed energy, let alone, a cursed technique somehow. That’s why I went all out on you after you beat my clones.”, Bendy continues. “It’s fine.”, Mugman says. “So, what’s the mission for today?”, Mugman asks. “Wait, hold on. Aren’t you still hurt or sore?”, Bendy asks, “I mean, you ARE in the infirmary for a reason that we both know.” “Actually, I feel pretty good. Those fingers Lion gave me must have helped with healing or something.” Mugman lied. With his new knowledge, he knew that it was Reversed Curse Technique that healed him so quickly, but he couldn’t just blatantly say that. “Well, if you say so. Anyway, we’re heading to a place that might have one of Jules fingers. This time, you’ll have to go in alone. If you are hurt, you gotta fall back or tag out.”,  Bendy said, showing Mugman the location on a map. “Got it. Lemme get changed real quick.”, Mugman said, as he walked out of the infirmary to ask Lion for his clothes. “Hey, Lion? Can I have my clothes-“, Mugman says, before a pen is thrown at Mugman. Mugman subconsciously activates Cleave, and gets rid of the pen. “Good reflexes, Mugman.”, Lion said, throwing ten more at him. Mugman Cleaves those too. Lion stands up, and says, “Good reflexes, Mugman. Hopefully you’ll use them in your solo mission.”, Lion says. “Yeah. Anywho, can I have my clothes?”, Mugman asks. Lion pulls out a laundry basket, and finds a student uniform labeled, “Mugman”, and hands it to Mugman. “Here is your new uniform, Mug. Uh, try not to ruin this, please? Students uniforms are expensive, and this one was made especially for you.”, Lion said nervously. Mugman checks the price tag to see that it cost seventeen thousand dollars for this one uniform.<br/>“Seventeen thousand?!” Mugman gasps, his eyes nearly popping out of his head. “That’s… that’s more than most cars!” “Yeah, that’s why we don’t want you to ruin it, so…please don’t?”, Lion asks again. Mugman gulps in nervousness. “Uhh, I’ll try my best.” Mugman walks out of Lions office. Then, he remembers a question he had for Lion. Well, it was two, but still. His first question was where was the mission gonna be, and his second question was to ask about what a Domain Expansion was, since he wasn’t really sure if he can trust the information in his head. “Uh, hey, Lion? I have a question. Well, it’s two. But, whatever.”, Mugman said, walking back into Lions office. “Alright, spit.”, Lion said. “Uh, where’s my mission gonna be today?”, Mugman asked. “Oh, it’s just an abounded mall just outside of Tokyo.”, Lion said, writing something down on a paper. “Okay. Oh, and…can you tell me what a Domain Expansion is? I heard you tell me it when you kidnapped me and tied me to a chair and discussed my options, but you never said anything beyond the name.”, Mugman asked. “Hmm…how do I explain this…The simplest way I can put it is like, having your own little word made up of your Cursed Energy. It’s a place made for you to use your technique. It also has a Sure Hit Effect. But, this requires a lot of cursed energy and focus.”, Lion explained. “Most beginners can’t use it once they begin, but they learn how to do it later on.”, Lion added. “Oh, okay.”, Mugman said. We then cut to the abandoned shop. “Alright Mugman. Remember, if you’re in trouble, fall out and call for help.”, Lion said. “Yeah, we’re right outside.”, Bendy said. “Yup.”, Cuphead said. “Wow, Cuphead, thanks for your shining enthusiasm.”, Mugman said sarcastically, before walking inside the shop. Mugman began to walk through the first floor of the mall, looking for the finger. “Man, this is creepy. And not like the creepy you see in cartoons.”, Mugman said. He kept on walking through the hallways, until he say the finger, sitting alone in a closed water fountain. However, the water was still running somehow. And it looked fresh. And the finger was inside it, just sitting there. “A trap, huh?”, Mugman said. He then smirked, and played dumb. “Oh, no! I sure do hope that there aren’t any cursed spirits around! After all, I’m only a grade FOUR sorcerer, oh, imagine the agony!”, Mugman said as he walked over to the fountain. Mugman reached the fountain, and reached for the finger reeeeaaaalllyyy slllooowwwllleeeyyy….”here I go, reaching for the special grade cursed object!”, Mugman said. Then, suddenly, a sharp water spike shot out of the ground, almost impaling Mugman hand. Mugman pulled back, and whipped out EWF. “Knew it.”, Mugman said, before the water based cursed spirit formed on the finger. “Alright, I just woke up, so would you be so kind as to hand over the finger now?”, Mugman said, holding out his hand. The sprit screeched at Mugman. Mugman grinned. “That’s what I hoped you’d say.”, Mugman said, signaling the curse to come at him. The curse sent out spiky water tendrils. But Mugman quickly zoomed through the air, cutting through them. Mugman made his way towards the cursed spirit, and tried to kick it, but went straight through it. Mugman crashed into a closed shop in the mall. “Right. It’s water.”, He said, before getting up and dusting himself off. “Alright. Let’s try this again, yeah?”, Mugman said, getting into a battle stance. The cursed sprit lunged at him. “Erase.”, Mugman said, pointing EWF at the cursed spirit. The cursed spirit was washed away, but it’ll be back in a matter of seconds. Mugman thought about how he could defeat a cursed spirit like this. He couldn’t use physical attacks. So, what now? Maybe he could…no, that’s too risky. Besides, he hasn’t even attempted it before. But, he knew he needed to get the finger, and impress his peers. Mugman gulped with nervousness, but put on a smile. “You know what?! Forget it!”, Mugman said, dropping EWF. The cursed spirit regenerated, and saw Mugman charging up his energy, but for what. Mugman then put his hands out, and called out, “Domain Expansion…”<br/>The cursed sprit looked in awe as the 2 meters surrounding them were enclosed in a black dome. Mugman closed his eyes, and continued his chant.<br/>“…Rigid Coffin of The Devil Himself.”<br/>Suddenly, the dome took form of a torture chamber, with knives, swords, stuck in the walls, and lava on the ground surrounding them both．”Look at that! It worked! However, it’s incomplete. I bet it’s ugly for most sorcerers. But it’ll have to do for now.”, Mugman said, seemingly talking to the cursed spirit. The cursed spirit panicked. “What’s wrong, spirit? You scared of a nine year old not knowing what he’s doing?”, Mugman said, mocking the spirit. “You’d better be. Dismantle.”, Mugman said, before a wave of lava cut the spirit in half, exorcising it. Mugman lowered his domain, and fell to one knee. “Damn, that took a lot out of me. But…I got the finger! And that’s all I need.”, Mugman said to himself, sweat pouring down his forehead. Suddenly, Mugman got a text from his phone.</div><br/><br/>LLM response:<br/><div style="
    background-color: #fff3e6;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>He checked his phone and saw a message from Lion, "Mission complete? Need aid?"</p>
<p>Mugman clumsily typed back with fingers that trembled from exertion, "Got it. Coming out."</p>
<p>Panting, Mugman rose to his feet and approached the fountain. He reached into the water, pulling out the now inert cursed finger, still wet from its eerie perch. He stuffed it into his pocket and headed toward the entrance of the abandoned mall.</p>
<p>As he emerged into the daylight, the rest of the group awaited him. Lion looked at Mugman with a mix of concern and pride, Bendy clapped his hands enthusiastically, and even Cuphead couldn't hide a pleased grin.</p>
<p>"Wow, Mugman! You look like you've been run over by a tractor. But you got it, huh?" Cuphead chuckled, poking fun in his typical brotherly fashion.</p>
<p>"Yeah, I did. It wasn't easy, though," Mugman said, managing a tired smile.</p>
<p>Lion approached him and placed a hand on his shoulder. "You did well. A solo mission on your first day as a sorcerer, and you executed a Domain Expansion—albeit incomplete, it's still impressive."</p>
<p>Bendy whistled, "An incomplete Domain Expansion on your first day? Man, what kind of monster are you?"</p>
<p>Mugman shrugged, exhaustion seeping into his every bone. "Guess I'm just lucky."</p>
<p>"Well, let's get you back to Jujutsu High. You need rest, and we need to report this. With that finger, we're one step closer to containing Jules completely," Lion said, ushering him back towards the car.</p>
<p>As they drove back, Mugman couldn't help but feel a mix of excitement and dread. He knew that with each finger he consumed, the presence of Jules grew stronger within him. He couldn't help but wonder, what did Jules really want with his body, and what was the true extent of the cursed king's power? </p>
<p>But for now, he pushed these thoughts aside. He had friends and teachers who had his back, and more immediately, he had a bed at Jujutsu High with his name on it for a well-deserved rest.</p></div>

