    line-height: 1.6;">Continue: Mugmans Jujutsu<br/>We open in on a Schoolyard, focusing on a thermometer. We then see a figure walk up to it, holding a phone, talking to someone on the other end. “A thermometer shed. You’re telling me someone’s keeping a special-grade cursed object in a place like this?”, the figure said, stepping out of the shadows to reveal Cuphead in a school uniform, though, it’s not a normal one. “Recovering it should be easy, then.”, the person says on the phone. Cuphead then walks over to the shed, and opens it. “The shed is empty.”, he says to the person on the phone. The person on the phone  asks, “what do you mean, ‘it’s empty’?” Cuphead sighs, and repeats, “It’s. Empty.” “For real? That’s funny.”, the person on the voice says. “I’m gonna punch you, Lion.”, Cuphead says to The person on the phone, revealed to be Lion. “No going home until it’s recovered, okay?”, Lion says over the phone, before hanging up. “Gonna hit you for real this time.”, Cuphead says, before hanging up. We then cut to the next day, where Mugman is using an Ouija Board. A Luigi board? A Yeegee board? Ouija board. “Dear spirits, please reveal if there is an animal who is stronger than me.”, then, the thing moves, spelling out, “C-A-R-P”. “Oh, man…”, Mugman mutters. Suddenly, Mugmans door crashes open, to reveal Cuphead, who came back from his midnight stroll. “Mugman, you didn’t submit any of your reports from your school club. Your school doesn’t have space and time for ghostbusters like your group.” He says, holding up an empty sheet of paper. “This is why I signed you up for the sports team, you have potential, but you’re not using it correctly.”, Cuphead states. “Well, what club do you participate in?”, Mugman asked. “Well, it’s a…private club, so I can’t tell you. But, rest assured that it’s as important as your…occult club.”, Cuphead responds. “Yeah, some club..”, Mugman mutters. Cuphead sees Mugman mope, and sighs in annoyance, before saying, “Okay, listen up, and good. Let’s have a gamble outside. If I win, you gotta do track. But, if I lose, I’ll give up on you. Deal?” Mugman thought, and then decided, “Sure, what challenge are we doing?” Cuphead pulled out a big metal ball, and said, “let’s see who can throw this the farthest.” “Deal.”, Mugman says. They head outside, and Cuphead throws the metal ball as hard as he can. “Fourteen meters, Cuphead!”, Bendy shouted, keeping score. “Alright, you’re up, Mugman.”, Cuphead said, expecting Mugman to throw it at least 10 feet in front of him. “Does it matter how I throw it?”, Mugman asked. “Go nuts, I don’t care.”, Cuphead said. Then, Mugman threw it, whizzing past everyone. “20 meters, Mugman! Holy shit, that’s far.”, Bendy yelled. “Well, I win! I don’t have to do anything! Yippee!”, Mugman yelled, running back inside. “Sigh…whatever…”, Cuphead said mopingly. Cuphead walked off. The next day at his school, Cuphead was trying to find that cursed object. “What’s with the rugby field?”, Cuphead said, looking up to see a scary spirit or a curse. “Is there’s a dead body or something?”, he said to himself, before he kept on walking. “Even so, I’d say it’s a grade 2 curse at best. I wonder what it has to do with the cursed object. I’d better hurry up and retrieve it. But, at the same time…”, Cuphead thought to himself, “it feels like it’s right in front of me, and far away at the same time. What a pain.” Cuphead kept on walking, trying to feel for the objects presence. “Still, I can’t look suspicious. I’ll probably get caught by some teacher or even worse, my brother will press me on what I’m doing.”, Cuphead thought. And just then, Mugman had walked past Cuphead, getting to one of his classes. Then, Cuphead felt it. The cursed object was inside Mugmans backpack. “What the hell, how does-how did-HOW DID MUGMAN FIND THAT CURSED OBJECT?!”, Cuphead thought, panicked. “I have to get it before some curse decides to attack Mugman, but how do I do that? I can’t just waltz up to him, and say ‘Hey, Mugman! So there’s a highly dangerous cursed object in your backpack that you didn’t know about and I need it to keep an even bigger curse from awakening or attack you. Can I have it?’, that’s stupid. Hmm…”, Cuphead thought,  before he got an idea. “I’ll just give him some food. And while he’s eating, I’ll take it. Easy.”, he thought. He walked over to Mugman, and tapped him on the shoulder. Mugman turned around, and Cuphead said to him, “Hey, Mugman. I’m not gonna eat this sandwich, you want it?” Mugman nodded, and took the sandwich. “Oh, I want to try something with this!”, Mugman said, before he reached into his backpack, and pulled out the cursed object. “I found this pickle in the boys bathroom. It was behind the toilet. It’s weird, because it looks like a finger, and it’s purple-ish. Maybe it’s a grape flavored pickle!”, he said. “Uh, Mugman-“, Cuphead said, but it was far too late. Mugman opened the sandwich, and slid in the cursed object into the sandwich. “Uh, MUGMAN-“, Cuphead tried to say. “WAIT! DONT TELL ME…I need mustard.”, Mugman said, opening back up the sandwich, and then putting mustard on it. And then, Mugman at the thing in one bite.<br/>“THAT’S A SPECIAL GRADE CURSED OBJECT! A LETHAL POSION! MUGMAN’LL DIE FOR SURE! But there’s a chance…a one in a million chance…”, Cuphead thought. Suddenly, strange markings began to appear on Mugman face, and Mugman normal smile became a malevolent grin. “The special grade cursed object incarnates!”, Cuphead thought. “Hehe…hee..hee..HAHAHAHAHAHAHAHA!”, the curse spoke through Mugman. “I KNEW IT! LIGHT IS BEST FELT WITH HUMAN SKIN!”, it continued, ripping off Mugman shirt. “WHERE ARE THE PEOPLE?! THE WOMEN, THE CHILDREN?!”, the curse spoke again. It then turned around. “WHAT A AGE IT HAS BECOME! WOMEN AND CHILDREN SPAWNING IN LIKE MAGGOTS! MARVELOUS! IT’LL BE A MASSACRE!”, it yelled, laughing maniacally. But then, it stopped itself. “Huh?!”, the curse said confused. “Hey, what are you doing with my body? Give it back!”, Mugman yelled. “How’re you able to move?”, it asked. “Uh…it IS my body, right??”, Mugman said. “I’m kinda like two-face.”, Mugman commented. “But…but I-“l the curse said, but Mugman cut him off. “Man, this guy inside me is annoying, but he’s also kinda weak.”, Mugman replied. “WEAK?! I’LL SHOW YOU WEAK!!”, it roared, but Mugman said, “SIR! I AM TRYING TO TALK TO MYSELF! SHUT UP!” “When I’m out of this body, you’ll be the first one I kill, you brat.”, it muttered. “Yeah, keep telling yourself that.”, Mugman said. “Mugman, don’t move. You’re no longer human. Under jujutsu regulations….i will exorcise the curse known as Mugman grace.”, Cuphead said. “Woah, Cuphead! Slow down! It’s not a problem. Furthermore, we’re both pretty messed up. We need a hospital or something.”, Mugman said with his hands up. “I can’t tell if that’s the curse or Mugman talking…damn, what should I do?!”, Cuphead thought. “What’s the situation?”, Lion asked. Cuphead then quickly turned around to see Lion, his teacher. “LION?! WHATRE YOU DOING HERE?!”, he yelled confused. “Well, I originally wasn’t gonna come, but after I heard about the cursed object, I came immediately. So, where is it?”, Lion stated, looking around casually. “Sorry…I ate it…”, Mugman said, walking over to Lion. “You’re not kidding. You have a curse inside you. Hmm…tell you what. Give up control to that curse inside you for…ten seconds. Then take control back. Got it?”, Lion asked. “Uh, okay…”, Mugman said. “But I’m not responsible for whatever this guy does in my body.”, Mugman added. “Hold this for me, Cuphead.”, Lion said, tossing Cuphead a bag. Cuphead caught it and looked inside. “Cookies? You were buying cookies while people were in danger??”, Cuphead asked annoyed. “Those are for the train ride home.”, Lion said. Then, the curse inside Mugman took control, and leaped up, preparing to attack Lion. Lion dodged, and the curse fell. “Since one of my students are watching, I’m gonna show off a bit. You don’t mind, right?”, Lion said, looking at the curse using Mugman. The curse frowned, before dashing away, and jumping back up into the air, swiping a claw at Lion. Lion dodged, and kicked the curse in the gut, before sending him flying into a wall. “8…9…10.”, Lion said aloud. Then, suddenly, The curses markings disappeared, and Mugman was back in control. “No way, you actually can control it!”, Lion said. “Yeah, but it’s kinda annoying. I can still hear his voice in my head.”, Mugman muttered. “That’s good. You can be a vessel.”, Lion said. Then, he swiftly knocked out Mugman. Mugman wakes up the next day, tied to a chair, with a bunch of papers with weird markings on the rope he’s tied with. “Wakes wakes, fingers and bakey.”, Lion said. “So, which one are you now?”, Lion asked. “Uh…it’s…me…Mugman.”, Mugman muttered. “Good. Time to break the news. And your decisions. Mugman…you’ve been set up for a secret execution.”, Lion said. “Huh?”, Mugman said. “Lemme explain. You see, Mugman, the cursed object that you had swallowed wasn’t a pickle. It was only one part of the king of curses; Jules. He was the strongest jujutsu sorcerer, and before he died, he had turned himself into twenty cursed objects. We have three, or four, counting the one side you. Here is one of the parts,” Lion said, pulling out a finger. Lion then threw it up into the air, and shot it with some cursed energy. “As you can see, it’s pretty tough, and also rare to find. And, with you swallowing one of those fingers, and not dying, you’ve become a vessel, with two options. One: we kill Jules inside you, and keep searching for the other fingers. Or…”, Lion said. “…or what?”, Mugman asked. “This is what I suggest. We find the rest of Jules-which is like…17 or 18 fingers-let him fully manifest inside you, and then execute you.” Lion proposed. “Either die right now, or die later, is basically what I’m asking.”, Lion said. “I…uh…”, Mugman stuttered. “…fine. I’ll eat the rest of Jules and then I’ll be executed.”, Mugman said. “Cool. Just know that in order to do this, you’ll have to enroll into Jujutsu High. And, acquire some cursed energy, and technique, and Domain Expansion, and cursed tool, and-“, Lion said, rambling on and on, before he saw Mugman just staring at him in confusion. “Let’s start with the school, first.”, Lion said, recognizing Mugmans confusion. We then cut to Lion and Mugman walking into the school. “Wow, this place looks very old. I can’t wait to make it look even uglier.”, Jules said, who had recently learned how to speak throw making little mouths on Mugman. “Sorry, Lion. He does that sometimes.”, Mugman said, covering the tiny mouth that Jules made. “It’s fine.”, Lion said. “Hey, Lion? I have a question.”, Mugman said, as they were walking towards the doors. “Between you and Jules…who would win?”, Mugman asked. Lion thought for a moment, before answering. “Well, if he were to get his full power back, he might cause me a little trouble.”, Lion said. Mugman asked, “but would you lose?” “Nah, I’d win.”, Lion said. “Tough talk coming from a brat.”, Jules said through one of the little mouths he had made on Mugman. Lion stopped walking, and asked, “what’s that supposed to mean?” “It’s just that you’re wrong. When I reach my peak status, not only will you not be able to handle me, but after I kill you, I’ll go after every single jujutsu sorcerer. Including this…brat I’m stuck inside currently.”, Jules said. “Wow, to be killed by the greatest curse in history. I’m touched.”, Lion said, sarcastically. After they talked with the principal, Mugman was enrolled. “Wait, so, how many sorcerers are at this school?”, Mugman said as Lion walked him to his room. “Like…eight students…”, Lion said nervously and awkwardly. “Oh.”, Mugman said. “But, some of your friends are here. Like, Alice, Bendy and Cuphead.”, Lion said. “Wait, what?! And they didn’t tell me?!”, Mugman said, angry. “Surprise.”, Lion said, before he opened Mugman room. “So, question for you, Mugman. Will you come on the missions for retrieving Jules’ fingers?”, Lion said, handing Mugman his stuff. Mugman thought for a moment, before he answered. “Yeah, I’ll help. Although, it would be funny to see a beat up Cuphead bring me fingers.”, Mugman said, before he chuckled. “Oh, really.”, Cuphead said, towering behind Mugman. “Uh…I didn’t mean that…Cuphead…”, Mugman said with an awkward grin. “Uh huh. Whatever. I’m also coming, Mugman.”, Cuphead said to Mugman. “What about your club, though?”, Mugman asked. Cuphead looked at Mugman in confusion, before answering. “Uh, Mugman? This IS the secret club.” “Oh.”, Mugman said. “So, Mugman. Since you’re coming on missions, you’ll probably need a weapon since you don’t have a cursed technique. Or, any cursed energy. Or anything cursed right now. So that’s why I’m giving you this.”, Lion said, before he pulled out a combat knife, and held it out to Mugman. It had a black fur guard and a brown handle. “This weapon is already imbued with cursed energy, so even you can use it.”, Lion said. “Woah…what’s it called?”, Mugman said, with a sparkle in his eye, looking at the knife. “Uh, we don’t have a name for it, but, it’s yours, so you can name it.”, Lion said, as Mugman took it. “I’ll name it…Earth, Wind and Fire.”, Mugman said. Cuphead snickered, before saying, “Wait, like, the band?” “Yeah, like the band. It came to me.”, Mugman said, slightly annoyed at Cupheads question. “Alright. Get cleaned up, and set up your room. In two days…”, Lion said.<br/>“…we’re heading to Tokyo.”, Lion added.<br/>We then cut to two days later, with Lion, Cuphead and Mugman arriving in the main part of Tokyo, Japan. “Hey, Lion? Who are we waiting for?”, Mugman asked, while he was holding a cup of beef ramen, and wearing cool sunglasses. “Oh, we’re waiting for bendy.”, Lion said, as he sipped some Japanese soda. “Bleh.”, Lion said, tasting the soda. “Well, how long ‘this gonna take? My feet hurt.”, Cuphead asked, as he was eating some potato chips. “I’d say one hour, five minutes, and seventeen seconds, starting…now!”, Lion said, as he took another sip from his soda. “Bleh.”, he said, tasting it again. “Why do you keep on drinking it if it tastes bad, Lion?”, Mugman asked. “It’s to keep my cursed energy up.”, Lion answered. “Huh?”, Mugman said confused. “Can you explain?”, Mugman asked Lion. “Alright, so, cursed energy fuels our attacks, right? But, the thing about cursed energy is that we need negative emotions to help channel it. That’s why I’m drinking it. It tastes unpleasant, and it fuels my cursed energy.”, Lion explains. “Wait, so, is Cuphead doing the same too?”, Mugman asked. “Yeah, I’m eating the worst flavor; Durian Fruit Flavored Potato Chips.”, Cuphead said. “Ew.” Mugman said. “Hey, guys! Am I late?”, Bendy said, walking through the crowd of people. But, bendy can’t get through. Then, he gets fed up, and he says, “VERB: STOP.” Then, suddenly, everyone stops in their tracks. Bendy moves through the crowd, and eventually makes it to his gang. “Verb: Continue.”, Bendy said, and then the crowd continues moving, not even noticing that they stopped. “WOAH, BENDY?! WHAT WAS THAT?!”, Mugman said in amazement. “Oh, it’s my cursed technique: Jagged Edge. Basically, I can pick from verbs, noun, exclamations, and adjectives, and use them. For example…Noun: Soda.”, Bendy explained, before a can of soda appeared in his hand. “See?”, Bendy asked. “Cursed…technique?”, Mugman asked confused. “Yeah, they’re basically our powers that we use to exorcise curses. Bendys  Cursed Technique, Jagged Edge, allows him to use his language to…uh…do that.” Lion explained. “Oh, alright. Then what’s yours and Cupheads cursed techniques?”, Mugman asked. “Mines called Survivor. It allows me to channel my cursed energy into certain parts of my body, and protect it or reinforce it. It can also double the damage I do.”, Lion said. “And what about you, Cuphead?”, Mugman asked. “Mine is called Beat It. It lets me move any surface around me, like manipulate it, along with turn any item, along with other items into an invention on the spot. I can also grab any tiny parts of a surface/machine, and shoot it at my opponent.”, Cuphead said. “Cool! When do I get mine?!”, Mugman asked, jumping up and down. “Not soon.”, Lion said. “Alright gang, follow me.”, Lion added, before walking off. “Oh…”, Mugman said, before dragging his feet and following Lion. Eventually, they reach an old building. “Alright. Bendy and Mugman. This is your test to see how strong you are. Whoever can exorcise the curse first gets a treat, paid for by me.”, Lion said. “Wait, what? What about the finger?”, Mugman asked. “Well, we need to see if you’re capable. So, like I said.”, Lion said. “Me and Cuphead here will spectate. Head on inside, and get that curse.”, Lion said, before sitting down. “Alright. See if you can keep up, Mugman!”, Bendy yelled, before in the blink of an eye, he dashed inside. “Woah, how did he move so fast?! Bendy can barely run within six feet of him without passing out!”, Mugman shouted. “It’s one of the additions that come with being a sorcerer. You also get your other physical feats leveled up the more cursed energy you have.”, Lion said. “Man…”, Mugman said, before quickly running inside. “You know…”, Cuphead said. “Mugman may die in there, Lion.” Lion glanced at Cuphead, before turning back and saying, “He’s strong. He’ll figure something out.” “And if he doesn’t?”, Cuphead asked. “We’ll help him.”, Lion said. We then cut to Mugman walking through the empty hallways of the building. “Man, this stinks. Figuratively and literally.”, Mugman said, as he was playing with Earth, Wind and Fire. Mugman then accidentally cuts his hand on Earth, Wind and Fire. “Ouch!”, Mugman said, as Earth, Wind, and Fire hit the ground. Then, suddenly, his wound heals, almost instantaneously. “Woah.”, Mugman said. Let me explain, real quick, to explain what happened. Mugman here just cut himself with a cursed tool. Cursed tools are imbued with cursed energy. Let’s just use numbers for an example. Let’s say that Earth, Wind and Fire has a cursed energy level of…two million. Not a lot for a cursed tool, but I’d say a little above average. When Mugman cut himself with Earth, Wind and Fire, he was imbued with…let’s say…half of that. So, he now has cursed energy, one million, to be exact. And, when he was imbued with the energy, he got so much a human couldn’t handle, that he reflexively performed Reverse Cursed Technique, which healed him. So, now Mugman can unlock his Cursed Technique, and become a sorcerer way earlier than he’s supposed to. But, he doesn’t know all this. Mugman stared at the wound, now healed. “That’s freaky.”, Mugman said to himself. Then,suddenly, he heard some groaning coming from another room. Mugman walked over to the room, to see a slug-like creature, or curse, staring at the clock. “WHAT…TIME IS IT?”, it said in a distorted voice. “It’s time…to get your butt kicked.”, Mugman muttered, before he pulled out Earth, Wind and Fire out of a knife holster on his leg. He dashed in the blink of an eye, behind the curse, and cut it in half, without even thinking. “WHAT THE SIGMA⁉️🔥🗣️🔥🗣️🗣️”, Mugman said, before he put back his weapon. “How did I-“, Mugman thought, before he heard Bendy walking towards the room, hearing the commotion. “Hey, Mugman, I heard a slash-“, Bendy said, before he saw the curse, cut in half. “…Say, Mugman…how did you defeat that curse…?”, Bendy asked. “I acted on instinct, I guess.”, Mugman said. “Instinct, huh?”, Bendy said. As quick as lighting, Bendy pulled out a sword, and swung at Mugman. Mugman, not even think, blocked it with Earth, Wind and Fire. “Let’s see how well you fight without any cursed energy.”, Bendy said, before he kicked Mugman into a desk behind him. Mugman avoided the desk and threw Earth, Wind and Fire at Bendy, before grabbing EWF (short for Earth, Wind and Fire), and slicing and dicing at Bendy several times at Bendy. “Don’t be scared. Close in.”, Mugman thought, as EWF and Bendys sword clashed multiple times. “Verb: Sharpen.”, Bendy said, before Mugman saw Bendys sword sharpen. Mugman kicked Bendys into a chalkboard, and continued to close in on bendy. Bendys grabbed some chalk by the chalkboard, and imbued it with some of his cursed energy, before saying, “Verb: Multiply. Verb: Sharpen.”, Before throwing 10 pieces of sharpened chalk at Mugman. Mugman quickly evaded all of them, with the only injury he sustained being a cut on his arm. Bendy grabbed his sword, and dashed out of the classroom, and racing up some stairs. Mugman quickly followed. Mugman made it to the top of the stairs, before he saw a hallway of abandoned lockers. Mugman walked past these lockers, as he held onto EWF tightly. “SUPRISE!”, Bendy shouted, lunging from one of the lockers, and kicking Mugman in the face, sending him flying. Mugman lands in another abandoned classroom. Bendy flies in, and bites on his sword, before saying, “Adjective: Duplicate. Time frame of twenty one seconds. Five exact copies. Starting now.” Suddenly, four more Bendys appeared beside the original Bendy, and lunged at Mugman. Mugman quickly realized he had to get rid of the four other Bendys quickly, and thought. And he thought quick. Mugman thought, “What do I do in this situation?” Suddenly, Mugmans cursed energy had focused on one of the Bendys, and Mugman instinctively said. “Dismantle.” Suddenly, the bendy clone that Mugmans energy focused on, was cut in half by one big slash caused by EWF. The other Bendys looked at the Ben-dy that was cut in half, and stopped in their tracks. They then looked at Mugman, who looked at another clone. “Cleave.”, Mugman said, and multiple grid like slices hit one of the Bendys clones, dicing the clone into cubes. “Mugman, how did you get a cursed technique with no cursed energy?”, Bendy asked, as he readied his sword.<br/>Mugman didn’t respond, and he cut through the two other Bendy clones, before saying, “Dismantle.” Again, sending a slice big enough to cut a person in two at bendy. Bendy blocked it with his sword, but Mugman used this chance to get behind bendy, and use Cleave to cut him all over his back. Bendy stabs his sword into the ground, and says, “VERB: EXPLODE!”, making the ground below Mugman and Bendy explode and fall, sending them falling into the abandoned schools cafeteria. Mugman jumps back and forth on the broken pieces of ground, dashing through the air to get to Bendy. Bendy starts backing up to get some distance, and he eventually makes it down to the ground. Bendy grabs onto a cafeteria table, and chucks it at Mugman. Mugman slices through it with a Dismantle slice, and then says, “Erase.”, before slicing the space in front of him to pull himself towards Bendy. Bendy blocks Mugman slice, and dashes away, before saying, “Verb: Ignite.” Bendys sword then catches fire, before he dashes towards Mugman. Mugman dashes towards Bendy, and the two clash. Bendy quickly pulls away, and Mugman falls forward, and it looks like Bendys is gonna stab Mugman. But at the last second, Bendys says, “Verb: Bind.”, Catching Mugman before he gets impaled on Bendys blade. Mugman catches his breath, and he quickly passes out due to exhaustion. Mugman then wakes up in his schools infirmary.<br/>“Wakey Wakey, Eggs and Bakey.”, Lion says. “What…Lion…?”, Mugman says groggily. Mugman tries to get up, but he winces in pain, as he falls back on the bed. “Easy there, Mugman. You’re pretty sore after your battle with Bendy. You did pretty good on the battlefield with no cursed energy.”, Lion said, holding a bowl of something. “Uh-“, Mugman tries to say something, but Lion shushes him. “Rest, Mugman. You need to eat.”, Lion says, before he opens to bowl lid to reveal three of Jules fingers. “But, eat these first, then talk, and then keep eating.”, Lion says. “Alright. Wait, so, I mistook these for a pickle? Man.”, Mugman comments, before taking one and swallowing it whole. Mugman then feels Jules curse inside him grow stronger. Mugman gags and laughs. “Ew! It’s so gross it makes you laugh.”, Mugman said, as he grabbed another. “So, how was Bendy?”, Lion asked as Mugman ate another finger. “Strong as hell! He moved so fast, and he could think real quick. But I’m quicker. I don’t know how I had lost.”, Mugman said, as he finished the last finger in the bowl. Mugman gagged again, while clutching his throat. “Well, Bendy is a second year, so he is more experienced with his technique.”, Lion said. “So, Mugman. How in the world did you get cursed energy AND a cursed technique?”, Lion asked seriously. “I don’t know. But I think it has something to do with this cut.”, Mugman said, before revealing his hand to Lion. “I accidentally cut myself with EWF, and my hand was instantly healed…somehow.”, Mugman continued. “Alright. Lemme see your technique though, I’m interested.”, lion said, before quickly dashing out of the room and bringing in a dummy. “Okay, be careful, though.”, Mugman said, holding out his hand. “Dismantle.”, Mugman said, before the dummy was sliced in half. Mugman then followed up with, “Cleave”, cutting the dummy into cubes. Then, Mugman got rid of the dummy by saying, “Erase.”, and erasing the dummy. “Cool, Mugman. This is a pretty powerful technique.”, Lion said.  “Thanks. I don’t have a name for it, though. Like you guys.”, Mugman said, lowering his hand. “How about…Purple Rain?”, Lion suggested while looking at some old music. “Hmm…sure.”, Mugman guessed, as he laid back down. “Get some rest. We’ll go on another mission for one of Jules fingers tomorrow if you’re okay.”, Lion said, before he left. Mugman nodded, and went to sleep. Mugman then woke up in some dream realm, staring face to face with Jules, the king of curses stuck inside his body. “Don’t worry, this is a dream. But I’m real.”, Jules said. “What…what do you want…?”, Mugman asked cautiously. “I want to make a deal with you, Mugman. Here’s the proposition: I give you some of my cursed energy, along with knowledge of cursed….anything that can help you in battle. This includes domain expansion, cursed techniques, cursed tools, binding vows, and heavenly restrictions. In return…whenever I say the word, ‘Enchant’, I can take control of your body for up to five minutes tops. That’s all I ask.”, Jules said. “Hell no! How do I know that-“, Mugman yelled, before Jules cut him off by saying, “within that time frame, I’m not allowed to harm or injure anybody. Does that seal the deal?” Mugman thought for a moment, before asking, “anything else I should be aware about?” “You will forget that you made this deal with me.”, Jules added. “So, our deal goes as follows: I get knowledge about domain expansion, cursed techniques, cursed tools, binding vows, and heavenly restrictions. and you get to take control of my body for five minutes whenever you say the word ‘Enchant’. I forget that we made this deal, and you can’t harm or injure anybody while you possess me. Am I right?”, Mugman recounted. “Yup.”, Jules said casually. “Do we have a deal?”, Jules asked. Mugman thought about this. Mugman thought really hard. “Why do you want to take control of my body if you can’t hurt anyone?”, Mugman asked. Jules slightly panicked, before answering Mugman, saying, “Fine. I agree.” Jules grins, his teeth showing. “Excellent. See you soon, Mugman. Literally.”, Jules said, shaking Mugman hand, before the dream ends. Mugman then wakes up in the infirmary. “Hey, Mugman. You alright?”, Bendy says, standing on a wall. “Sorry that I attacked you yesterday. Lion wanted me to test you. See how good you were. I didn’t expect you to have cursed energy, let alone, a cursed technique somehow. That’s why I went all out on you after you beat my clones.”, Bendy continues. “It’s fine.”, Mugman says. “So, what’s the mission for today?”, Mugman asks. “Wait, hold on. Aren’t you still hurt or sore?”, Bendy asks, “I mean, you ARE in the infirmary for a reason that we both know.” “Actually, I feel pretty good. Those fingers Lion gave me must have helped with healing or something.” Mugman lied. With his new knowledge, he knew that it was Reversed Curse Technique that healed him so quickly, but he couldn’t just blatantly say that. “Well, if you say so. Anyway, we’re heading to a place that might have one of Jules fingers. This time, you’ll have to go in alone. If you are hurt, you gotta fall back or tag out.”,  Bendy said, showing Mugman the location on a map. “Got it. Lemme get changed real quick.”, Mugman said, as he walked out of the infirmary to ask Lion for his clothes. “Hey, Lion? Can I have my clothes-“, Mugman says, before a pen is thrown at Mugman. Mugman subconsciously activates Cleave, and gets rid of the pen. “Good reflexes, Mugman.”, Lion said, throwing ten more at him. Mugman Cleaves those too. Lion stands up, and says, “Good reflexes, Mugman. Hopefully you’ll use them in your solo mission.”, Lion says. “Yeah. Anywho, can I have my clothes?”, Mugman asks. Lion pulls out a laundry basket, and finds a student uniform labeled, “Mugman”, and hands it to Mugman. “Here is your new uniform, Mug. Uh, try not to ruin this, please? Students uniforms are expensive, and this one was made especially for you.”, Lion said nervously. Mugman checks the price tag to see that it cost seventeen thousand dollars for this one uniform.<br/>“Seventeen thousand?!” Mugman gasps, his eyes nearly popping out of his head. “That’s… that’s more than most cars!” “Yeah, that’s why we don’t want you to ruin it, so…please don’t?”, Lion asks again. Mugman gulps in nervousness. “Uhh, I’ll try my best.” Mugman walks out of Lions office. Then, he remembers a question he had for Lion. Well, it was two, but still. His first question was where was the mission gonna be, and his second question was to ask about what a Domain Expansion was, since he wasn’t really sure if he can trust the information in his head. “Uh, hey, Lion? I have a question. Well, it’s two. But, whatever.”, Mugman said, walking back into Lions office. “Alright, spit.”, Lion said. “Uh, where’s my mission gonna be today?”, Mugman asked. “Oh, it’s just an abounded mall just outside of Tokyo.”, Lion said, writing something down on a paper. “Okay. Oh, and…can you tell me what a Domain Expansion is? I heard you tell me it when you kidnapped me and tied me to a chair and discussed my options, but you never said anything beyond the name.”, Mugman asked. “Hmm…how do I explain this…The simplest way I can put it is like, having your own little word made up of your Cursed Energy. It’s a place made for you to use your technique. It also has a Sure Hit Effect. But, this requires a lot of cursed energy and focus.”, Lion explained. “Most beginners can’t use it once they begin, but they learn how to do it later on.”, Lion added. “Oh, okay.”, Mugman said. We then cut to the abandoned shop. “Alright Mugman. Remember, if you’re in trouble, fall out and call for help.”, Lion said. “Yeah, we’re right outside.”, Bendy said. “Yup.”, Cuphead said. “Wow, Cuphead, thanks for your shining enthusiasm.”, Mugman said sarcastically, before walking inside the shop. Mugman began to walk through the first floor of the mall, looking for the finger. “Man, this is creepy. And not like the creepy you see in cartoons.”, Mugman said. He kept on walking through the hallways, until he say the finger, sitting alone in a closed water fountain. However, the water was still running somehow. And it looked fresh. And the finger was inside it, just sitting there. “A trap, huh?”, Mugman said. He then smirked, and played dumb. “Oh, no! I sure do hope that there aren’t any cursed spirits around! After all, I’m only a grade FOUR sorcerer, oh, imagine the agony!”, Mugman said as he walked over to the fountain. Mugman reached the fountain, and reached for the finger reeeeaaaalllyyy slllooowwwllleeeyyy….”here I go, reaching for the special grade cursed object!”, Mugman said. Then, suddenly, a sharp water spike shot out of the ground, almost impaling Mugman hand. Mugman pulled back, and whipped out EWF. “Knew it.”, Mugman said, before the water based cursed spirit formed on the finger. “Alright, I just woke up, so would you be so kind as to hand over the finger now?”, Mugman said, holding out his hand. The sprit screeched at Mugman. Mugman grinned. “That’s what I hoped you’d say.”, Mugman said, signaling the curse to come at him. The curse sent out spiky water tendrils. But Mugman quickly zoomed through the air, cutting through them. Mugman made his way towards the cursed spirit, and tried to kick it, but went straight through it. Mugman crashed into a closed shop in the mall. “Right. It’s water.”, He said, before getting up and dusting himself off. “Alright. Let’s try this again, yeah?”, Mugman said, getting into a battle stance. The cursed sprit lunged at him. “Erase.”, Mugman said, pointing EWF at the cursed spirit. The cursed spirit was washed away, but it’ll be back in a matter of seconds. Mugman thought about how he could defeat a cursed spirit like this. He couldn’t use physical attacks. So, what now? Maybe he could…no, that’s too risky. Besides, he hasn’t even attempted it before. But, he knew he needed to get the finger, and impress his peers. Mugman gulped with nervousness, but put on a smile. “You know what?! Forget it!”, Mugman said, dropping EWF. The cursed spirit regenerated, and saw Mugman charging up his energy, but for what. Mugman then put his hands out, and called out, “Domain Expansion…”<br/>The cursed sprit looked in awe as the 2 meters surrounding them were enclosed in a black dome. Mugman closed his eyes, and continued his chant.<br/>“…Rigid Coffin of The Devil Himself.”<br/>Suddenly, the dome took form of a torture chamber, with knives, swords, stuck in the walls, and lava on the ground surrounding them both．”Look at that! It worked! However, it’s incomplete. I bet it’s ugly for most sorcerers. But it’ll have to do for now.”, Mugman said, seemingly talking to the cursed spirit. The cursed spirit panicked. “What’s wrong, spirit? You scared of a nine year old not knowing what he’s doing?”, Mugman said, mocking the spirit. “You’d better be. Dismantle.”, Mugman said, before a wave of lava cut the spirit in half, exorcising it. Mugman lowered his domain, and fell to one knee. “Damn, that took a lot out of me. But…I got the finger! And that’s all I need.”, Mugman said to himself, sweat pouring down his forehead. Suddenly, Mugman got a text from his phone.</div><br/><br/>LLM response:<br/><div style="
    background-color: #fff3e6;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>He checked his phone and saw a message from Lion, "Mission complete? Need aid?"</p>
<p>Mugman clumsily typed back with fingers that trembled from exertion, "Got it. Coming out."</p>
<p>Panting, Mugman rose to his feet and approached the fountain. He reached into the water, pulling out the now inert cursed finger, still wet from its eerie perch. He stuffed it into his pocket and headed toward the entrance of the abandoned mall.</p>
<p>As he emerged into the daylight, the rest of the group awaited him. Lion looked at Mugman with a mix of concern and pride, Bendy clapped his hands enthusiastically, and even Cuphead couldn't hide a pleased grin.</p>
<p>"Wow, Mugman! You look like you've been run over by a tractor. But you got it, huh?" Cuphead chuckled, poking fun in his typical brotherly fashion.</p>
<p>"Yeah, I did. It wasn't easy, though," Mugman said, managing a tired smile.</p>
<p>Lion approached him and placed a hand on his shoulder. "You did well. A solo mission on your first day as a sorcerer, and you executed a Domain Expansion—albeit incomplete, it's still impressive."</p>
<p>Bendy whistled, "An incomplete Domain Expansion on your first day? Man, what kind of monster are you?"</p>
<p>Mugman shrugged, exhaustion seeping into his every bone. "Guess I'm just lucky."</p>
<p>"Well, let's get you back to Jujutsu High. You need rest, and we need to report this. With that finger, we're one step closer to containing Jules completely," Lion said, ushering him back towards the car.</p>
<p>As they drove back, Mugman couldn't help but feel a mix of excitement and dread. He knew that with each finger he consumed, the presence of Jules grew stronger within him. He couldn't help but wonder, what did Jules really want with his body, and what was the true extent of the cursed king's power? </p>
<p>But for now, he pushed these thoughts aside. He had friends and teachers who had his back, and more immediately, he had a bed at Jujutsu High with his name on it for a well-deserved rest.</p></div>

