    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>Unemployment can have a devastating impact on immigrants, who are already facing the challenges of adjusting to a new country. Without a steady source of income, immigrants may struggle to provide for their families, find stable housing, or access quality healthcare. The stress and uncertainty of unemployment can also take a toll on their mental and emotional well-being, leading to feelings of isolation and hopelessness. Furthermore, being unable to find work may hinder their ability to fully integrate into their new community and achieve the American Dream they came to pursue. Overall, the high levels of unemployment among immigrants can exacerbate the social misery that Jane Addams spoke of, creating a cycle of poverty and hardship that is difficult to break.</p></div>

